  "prompt": "What is the origin of the word news?",
  "response": "The word \"news\" originates from the Middle English word \"newes,\" which is the plural form of \"new.\" It is derived from the Old English word \"neowe\" or \"niwe,\" which means \"new.\" Essentially, \"news\" refers to new information or fresh tidings about recent events. The usage of the word in this context began to emerge around the 14th century. Typically, news constitutes reports of recent happenings, noteworthy events, or important information that is being shared with the public.",
